🔒 Constraint
15 listening hours / month
5 months
Goal: sharper judgment, discipline, leverage — not inspiration
Rule:
One primary book per month.
Optional short secondary only if time remains.
No parallel listening.

📅 5-MONTH LISTENING PLAN (OPTIMIZED)
Month 1 — Focus & Attention (Foundation)
Deep Work – Cal Newport – 7h 45m
The Obstacle Is the Way – Ryan Holiday – 4h 39m
⏱ ~12h 25m
🎯 Build attention as identity + execution under friction

Month 2 — Clear Thinking & Time Reality
Clear Thinking – Shane Parrish – 6h 42m
Four Thousand Weeks – Oliver Burkeman – 6h 14m
⏱ ~12h 56m
🎯 Fewer bad decisions, less overplanning, sharper filters

Month 3 — Biology & Stability
Why We Sleep – Matthew Walker – 13h 52m
⏱ ~13h 52m
🎯 Sleep = discipline multiplier (non-negotiable infrastructure)

Month 4 — Power, Incentives, Communication
7 Rules of Power – Jeffrey Pfeffer – 6h 13m
Supercommunicators – Charles Duhigg – 7h 29m
⏱ ~13h 42m
🎯 Real-world power dynamics + precise communication

Month 5 — Identity & Self-Image
Psycho-Cybernetics – Maxwell Maltz – 12h 16m
Stoicism – Jason Hemlock – 2h 49m (optional if time remains)
⏱ ~15h (max)
🎯 Install disciplined self-image + emotional regulation


🎧 HOW TO LISTEN (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
Only while walking / chores
No background listening
Pause when behavior shifts
After each session, write one line only:
“This changes my behavior by ___.”
If no behavior changes → stop the book.

🧠 PERSONA RULE
Information is only useful if it removes future stupidity.
This plan does that.
Save this as your index card.
Do not optimize it further.
When Month 1 begins, you start with Deep Work — nothing else.
